task.summary: Default task
Added all of the new Tiles to the AssetLoader and MapLoader. Also fixed some bugs with Entity
While the renderer maintains the batch and the shaperender, it does not start or end them.
Added Chest
Moved Inventory and inventory contents into a new package Moved BattleCharacter, Party, and subclasses into a new subpackage Added Chest Entity
Armor, Weapon, Item, and SpecialItem now all subclass AbstractItem AbstractItem has a universal ID, name, and value Modified get method in Inventory Began implementing chest entities
Removed getSprite() from Renderable Sprites are no longer handled by Entity, and the getSprite(runtime) method must be defined in the subclass

PreBattle is no longer a thing. Instead, a Dialogue can have a postInteraction that occurs concluding the dialogue. This and DialogueOptions are mutually exclusive. Added openChest, closeChest, and takeItem interactions. Chests should now be fully functional and should properly interface with Inventory Changed InteractionUtils.generic(Object object) into InteractionUtils.create(Object... objects), and added new Interactions to its methodology It can now process interactions that have multiple parameters
MapCharacter constructor now requires facingSprites and facingAnimations. Subclasses modified appropriately
Minor temporary tweak until we have large character textures
Updated the dimension on the Weyerhauser Sprite
Fixed building tile keys in MapLoader
Updated the loadCharacter method based on the current schema for character canvases
Updated the loadCharacter method based on the current schema for character canvases
Updated the loadCharacter method based on the current schema for character canvases
Discovered and used the TextureRegion.split(Texture, int, int) method for character breakdown
Fixed tree tiles
Fixed tree tiles Added a big tree to the map to test out large tiles
Generated equals methods in Plot and Goal The equals method in goal partially relies on Interaction.equals, which I cannot override so it must be the exact same interaction reference

Heavily overhauled Interaction. It now has 2 parameters (primary and secondary) of generic type U, V. Static Interaction creator methods set U and V appropriately, and the input(s) to the method are passed into the constructor. This has two benefits: first, the parameters are actually stored in the Interaction, which is ideal. Second, because of the first, I can write a equals() method based on the two parameters.
I have put the part of the Map we current have into the file, and booted it up into the game. It's pretty cool
Implemented continuous movement for the main character, meaning that if you hold down a direction, you will move that way until you let go or hit something impassable
Aside from lacking building Sprites and Entities, the map is in place and completed (excluding the block north of Grand)
Aesthetic changes
Fixed (after much strife and frustration) the bug where building sprites would disappear
Added SpriteUtils for dealing with annoying TextureRegion functions, like the buggy split method
Fixed a bug in one of the split methods.
Tweaked the map a bit

BattleController now retrieves items from inventory
Added another simplifier method to InteractionUtils
Added another simplifier method to InteractionUtils
Fixed some things with the map sprites not rendering properly
Increased character move speed for debugging efficiency
Renamed Controllers Updated Battle a bit (formerly BattleController) Added a float delta parameter to BattleAction.run for future use
Added the campus map to git. Not really important, but it was the logical place to put it

Added getNearestValidLocation methods to both Grid and Location These methods find a valid location by starting at the initial position (or the nearest valid position to that position) and recursively move in the given direction until it finds a pathable position. If it runs into the far end of the map, it will return null, though this not-found case is incredibly unlikely. Currently, this method is only used by Entity.putInGrid, which calls it on the input location (unless it is null) to put the entity in at a pathable location
fixed some map tiles

Created a Parser class. It reads files and generates a ParsedObject. The ParsedObject stores the name, object descriptor, map of parameters, and data (an array of strings) The descriptor is of type Leader. Leader simply describes any possible leader that could be used in the file The parameter map maps leaders to String values, though the ParsedObject provides methods to convert a parameter into an int, a float, or a boolean
Made Interaction constructors public, as they should be
Added some javadoc to the Parser
